    Find the smallest number larger than X consisting of the same digits as X.

    Args:
    stdin: str - the input integer X.

    Returns:
    str: the output number, or 0 if no such number exists.
    """
    x = int(stdin)
    x_digits = sorted(str(x))
    x_length = len(x_digits)

    # Edge case: if all digits in x are the same, there is no number larger than x.
    if len(set(str(x))) == 1:
        return "0"

    # Find the index of the largest digit in x.
    max_index = -1
    for i in range(x_length - 1, -1, -1):
        if x_digits[i] != x_digits[x_length - 1]:
            max_index = i
            break

    # If the largest digit is at the beginning, there is no number larger than x.
    if max_index == 0:
        return "0"

    # Swap the largest digit with the smallest digit to the right of it.
    x_digits[max_index], x_digits[max_index + 1] = x_digits[max_index + 1], x_digits[max_index]

    # Sort the digits to the right of the largest digit in ascending order.
    x_digits[max_index + 1:] = sorted(x_digits[max_index + 1:])

    return "".join(x_digits)
